<p>China’s economy grew 4.8% year on year in the third quarter of 2025, its slowest pace in a year, according to official data [washingtonpost.com#1][ft.com#1][bbc.com#1][ndtv.com#1]. The slowdown reflects pressure from heightened trade tensions and tariffs with the United States, a prolonged property downturn, and softer consumer spending [ft.com#1][bbc.com#1][michaelwest.com.au#1]. Even so, the reading keeps growth broadly on course for Beijing’s roughly 5% full‑year target, though economists say more policy support is needed to strengthen domestic demand [scmp.com#1]. Analysts note the economy has avoided a sharp downturn while working through structural drags [bbc.com#1][ft.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/xKY60FC9jsff6yD5F9Z4FZ_jUJFwwxq5pzku0c928PNPnZVBqP4-yk713r2BaD0DvZCPRrkswnxi6y31AFOzaUn7WnYRc8AscOca4ljh2IwOnMwRX64KdcCkZxiS01Jnzm_n5kBNnpk8ImGafnJHjYB5-wxTZGPQg57E6E-EkViTmi_m' alt='Firstpost coverage image on China&#x27;s Q3 GDP slowdown.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Quarterly momentum: On a quarter-on-quarter basis, GDP rose 1.1% in Q3, exceeding a 0.8% forecast and edging above a revised 1.0% in Q2 [michaelwest.com.au#1].</li><li>Comparative pace: Year-on-year growth eased from 5.2% in the previous quarter, marking the weakest annual pace since Q3 2024 [michaelwest.com.au#1].</li><li>Forecast context: The 4.8% result roughly matched expectations and was slightly above a 4.76% economist survey by a Chinese data provider, while aligning with a Reuters-polled 4.8% median [scmp.com#1][michaelwest.com.au#1].</li><li>Data timing: The National Bureau of Statistics released the figures on Monday as top leaders began an important planning meeting for the months ahead [scmp.com#1][washingtonpost.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Analysts: Further policy support is needed to maintain the stable trajectory and strengthen domestic demand. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/economy/economic-indicators/article/3329606/china-reports-48-quarterly-gdp-growth-moving-closer-annual-target'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Financial Times analysis: Escalating trade tensions and the property downturn are weighing on momentum. (<a href='https://www.ft.com/content/72fb154c-44a5-4777-98da-cee92a052369'>Financial Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/10/20/china-economy-gdp-growth/'>China’s economy grows at slowest pace in a year as trade war bites</a> - washingtonpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/economy/economic-indicators/article/3329606/china-reports-48-quarterly-gdp-growth-moving-closer-annual-target'>China reports 4.8% quarterly GDP growth, moving closer to annual target</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/72fb154c-44a5-4777-98da-cee92a052369'>China’s economy expands at slowest pace in a year</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://michaelwest.com.au/china-q3-gdp-growth-slows-to-4-8-per-cent/'>China Q3 GDP growth slows to 4.8 per cent</a> - michaelwest.com.au</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/chinas-economic-growth-slows-to-4-8-in-the-3rd-quarter-ws-e-13943565.html'>China’s economic growth slows to 4.8% in the 3rd quarter</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c9v1medkk3vo'>China&#x27;s economic growth slows as trade tensions with US flare up</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/chinas-economic-growth-slows-to-lowest-in-a-year-at-4-8-amid-trumps-trade-tensions-9486166#publisher=newsstand'>China&#x27;s Economic Growth Slows To Lowest In A Year At 4.8% Amid Trade Tensions</a> - ndtv.com</li></ul>